== Manga ==
*The manga is serialized in [[Comp Ace]] as ".hack//Quantum+" (pronounced "Quantum Plus"). Illustrated by {{nihongo|Nao Mitaka|三鷹ナオ}}, and will follow the story as written for the anime by Kinema Citrus. 
*Another manga was released in March 2011, titled {{nihongo|'''''(.hack//Quantum introduction)'''''|.hack//Quantum I (イントロダクション)}}, and it was illustrated by SOGA Atsushi. This manga is a prologue to the events of the OVA series, and the first two chapters can be accessed freely in the Comic Gekkin website (owned by [[Bandai Visual]]).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.comic-gekkin.com/works/hackquantum/ |title=Comic Gekkin website |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130310051809/http://www.comic-gekkin.com/works/hackquantum/ |archivedate=2013-03-10 |deadurl=yes |df= |access-date=2018-11-29 }}</ref> The third chapter can be accessed only from a [[NTT DoCoMo]] phone. Later, a printed version was released by Emotion Comics.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/4048992317 |title=Amazon.co.jp： ．ｈａｃｋ／／Ｑｕａｎｔｕｍ Ｉ（ｉｎｔｒｏｄｕｃｔｉｏｎ） (Emotion Comics 31): 曽我 篤士, ．ｈａｃｋ Ｃｏｎｇｌｏｍｅｒａｔｅ・Ｑｕａｎｔｕｍ Ｐｒｏｊｅｃｔ: 本 |publisher=Amazon.co.jp |date= |accessdate=2013-05-24}}</ref>

