{{About|the Sami publication|the Lule Sámi Center|Árran}}
{{italic title}} {{refimprove|date=April 2017}}
'''''Árran''''' is an English language quarterly of Sami culture and news. The editor of ''Árran'' is Evelyn Ashford, successor to long-time editor Arden Johnson. ''Árran'' was founded by the late Mel Olsen in 1995.{{Citation needed|reason=citation needed to prove claim|date=May 2014}} Published by the [[Sami Siida of North America]] (SSNA), the newsletter is by and for Sami North Americans and friends. ''Árran'' headquarters are in [[Minneapolis, Minnesota]]. The SSNA council makes up the editorial advisory board.
The word ''árran'' refers to the fire in the center of the [[lavvu]], the iconic tent-symbol of Sami cultures. Issues contain articles relating to Sami culture and identity, poetry, and news from [[Sápmi (area)|Sápmi]] by contributors from Sápmi and North America. ''Árran'' also has a companion blog, currently under a remodeling program.
==See also== *''[[Báiki]]'' an English journal about Sami issues in northern America. *[[Sami Siida of North America]] a network for Sami in North America.
